messages: In my dream, I was being groomed by a classy old lady. She smiled serenely and took an apple from somewhere and handed it to me.
I dreamed that I was at a table in the great hall of a mansion with food on the table while musicians played elegant music.
In my dream, I was being ordered to do chores by an old gentleman. He seemed somewhat irritated as he stared at me without moving a single muscle of his facial expression.
I dreamed that I was cleaning up the dishes that I had finished eating in the hall of a mansion while the musicians were playing some somber music.
The endless stone corridor, I was lighting each of the candlesticks there. Crawling through the darkness, I silently continued that task. Everywhere, everywhere, everywhere. ......
I dreamt that I was in the great hall of a mansion, arranging freshly caught food, while a cacophony of musicians played. If you look closely, you will see that it was me who was laid out.
I was a cellular body, and something tore me apart, and I became us. Eventually we began to divide rapidly, one me into a fish, one me into a lizard, one me into a cat.
I dreamed that I was holding my new master against the corpse of my old master. Ah, freedom is wonderful.
